    {
      "connection-type": "all",
      "desc": "A minimum of eight subjects (96 units) beyond the introductory course, pre-thesis, and thesis. Remaining subjects include two language subjects (must be in the same language) in Area I (or equivalent proficiency), and seven subjects selected from at least two of the three disciplinary areas (Areas II-IV). Two language subjects beginning at Levels III and IV, either in Spanish or Portuguese, satisfy the Area I language requirement. MIT offers Levels III and IV of Spanish every semester and offers Level III of Portuguese every fall semester and Level IV every spring semester. Students who demonstrate competence beyond Level IV may either take two advanced language subjects (highly recommended) or two more subjects from Areas II, III, and IV. Students who are not required to take Area I subjects and opt not to take advanced language subjects must take all subjects from Areas II, III, and IV, with at least one subject from each area.",
